# Coverage exclusions — regex patterns matched against lines of the
# raw `go test -coverprofile` output, applied before the 100% gate
# by covgate (https://github.com/kfet/covgate).
#
# Convention: file-level patterns only. No line numbers, no
# per-function regexes — both rot on any nearby edit.

# Per-feature `<feature>_must.go` files. Each holds the `mustX` helpers
# for the feature in `<feature>.go`: tiny wrappers that panic on
# structurally-unreachable error paths. Keeping them in a sibling file
# means the helper sits next to the code that uses it, the name signals
# intent (`mustStdoutPipe`, …), and the file-level coverage exclusion
# stays narrow and meaningful.
_must\.go:

# Windows-only build of the procgroup helper: empty function body,
# can't be covered by the macOS/Linux CI runners.
^github.com/kfet/pinexec/procgroup_windows\.go:
